\i Ritenour 
\i0 and 
\i Adams
\i0 . Further, Plaintiff\'92s behavior is strikingly similar to that which the 
\i Ritenour 
\i0 Court found sufficient to support the employer\'92s summary judgment motion.\
As the undisputed facts show, Plaintiff\'92s failure to notify Dracon\'92s human resources manager of his absences was a rapidly worsening problem that left her no choice but to let him go, despite his value to the company. Plaintiff\'92s history of absenteeism and repeated failure to meet his obligations under Dracon\'92s sick leave policy are precisely the kind of behavior that the Sixth Circuit Court of Appeals has found constitutes lawful grounds for termination.}